  "prompt": "Is there an Android application that I can use to lookup words anywhere on my phone, without needing to have the application opened?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several Android applications that allow you to look up words anywhere on your phone without needing to have the application opened. One popular option is \"Google Translate,\" which offers a feature called Tap to Translate. This feature allows you to translate text from any app by simply copying it to your clipboard, and a translation pop-up will appear.\n\nAnother option is \"Instant Dictionary: Word Lookup,\" which provides a floating icon that you can use to look up words without leaving the current app. You can simply tap on the floating icon, type in the word, and get the definition instantly.\n\nAdditionally, \"Bluelight Dictionary\" offers a similar functionality where you can look up words using a floating widget.\n\nThese applications provide convenient ways to look up words on-the-fly without interrupting your workflow or having to switch between apps.",
